{"ts":"2026-07-19T03:42:52.037Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"append","patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"/body","value":"GH-608. Disjoint-field concurrent edits (A: title, B: body) always conflict solely on the shared updated_at scalar every pm update rewrites. Most common cooperative case, fails 100%. Distinct from pm-9q2t (count headers) and pm-wc1r (history chain). Fix direction: deterministic updated_at resolution (max-wins merge driver) or serialization that isolates volatile scalars from semantic fields."},{"op":"replace","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-19T03:42:52.037Z"}],"before_hash":"b764cecb67f5e44e42ced176951df89ce56e5ee912b016e51a2e7bea72123bd7","after_hash":"694f64c29b25680aeca894bb6561c5cbcd8225c78ef9b708e094db39eb51ee82"}
